				<div style="font-style:italic">I have heard from many objective sources that we would be maintaining a human colony on mars right now, enjoying the fringe benefits of all the technology developed as a result. But a small and relatively insignificant number of accidents, as they relate to other worldly events, have all but halted any progress in space exploration<br />
<br />
