<br />
Take for example that some wild sci-fi sounding technologies that where originally the territory of private enthusiasts and underestimated visionaries, saw their greatest progress during the few moments in world history where Progress trumped Risk Aircraft in WWI, &amp; Computers and Nuclear Science in WWII for example Also the resulting Internet backbone and Space Program in the Depths of the Cold War<br />
<br />
My question then is: <br />
<b>In your opinion, when is progress, if ever, more important then potential risk? And do you have an example why or why-not?</b></div>
			
