</div>Um, no. Our aviation capabilities at the time of Pearl Harbor barely let us pull off a small raid, and that only worked because it was the first time and because we were willing to crash land the planes in China. We had no ability to mount large-scale bombing of Japan until 1945, and only then because we conducted an island-hopping campaign for 2 1/2 years to obtain air fields within striking distance of the Japanese homeland and had killed almost all of Japan's skilled fighter pilots by then.</div>
